			    STPJS 247</div>
  <p class="cont">wine,&rdquo;<span class="footRef">1</span> and we shall finally have to come to the same conclusion that Paul did&mdash;&ldquo;No man knows
  the things of God but by the Spirit of God;&rdquo;<span class="footRef">2</span> for with the great revelations of Paul when he was
  caught up into the third heaven and saw things that were not lawful to utter,<span class="footRef">3</span> no man was apprised
  of it until he mentioned it himself fourteen years after; and when John had the curtains of heaven
  withdrawn,<span class="footRef">4</span> and by vision looked through the dark vista of future ages, and contemplated events that
  should transpire throughout every subsequent period of time, until the final winding up
  scene<span class="footRef">5</span>&mdash;while he gazed upon the glories of the eternal world, saw an innumerable company of
  angels<span class="footRef">6</span> and heard the voice of God&mdash;it was in the Spirit, on the Lord&rsquo;s day,<span class="footRef">7</span> unnoticed and
  unobserved by the world.</p>
  <p class="wideEllipse">* * *</p>

  <div class="topic">The Necessity of Prayer</div>
  <p class="std">The Lord cannot always be known by the thunder of His voice,<span class="footRef">8</span> by the display of His glory or
  by the manifestation of His power, and those that are the most anxious to see these things, are the
  least prepared to meet them,<span class="footRef">9</span> and were the Lord to manifest His powers as He did to the children of
  Israel,<span class="footRef">10</span> such characters would be the first to say, &ldquo;Let not the Lord speak any more, lest we His
  people die.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">11</span></p>
  <p class="std">We would say to the brethren, seek to know God in your closets,<span class="footRef">12</span> call upon him in the fields.<span class="footRef">13</span>
  Follow the directions of the Book of Mormon, and pray over, and for your families, your cattle, your
  flocks, your herds, your corn, and all things that you possess; ask the blessing of God upon all your
  labors, and everything that you engage in.<span class="footRef">14</span> Be virtuous and pure;<span class="footRef">15</span> be men of integrity and truth;<span class="footRef">16</span>
  keep the commandments of God;<span class="footRef">17</span> and then you will be able more perfectly to understand the
  difference between right and wrong&mdash;between the things of God and the things of men;<span class="footRef">18</span> and your
  path will be like that of the just, which shineth brighter and brighter unto the perfect day.<span class="footRef">19</span></p>
  <div class="topic">The True Use of Tongues</div>
  <p class="std">Be not so curious about tongues, do not speak in tongues except there be an interpreter
  present;<span class="footRef">20</span> the ultimate design of tongues is to speak to foreigners,<span class="footRef">21</span> and if persons are very anxious
  to display their intelligence, let them speak to such in</p>
